					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex; Sefardi square script, punctuated.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>217 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>240</height>
										<width>175</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>217 folios (+ 1 unfoliated modern and 1 older paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>28 quires: i6 (folios 1-6), ii7(folios 7-13), iii-xxvii8 (folios 14-213), xxviii5 (folios 214-217). </p>
									<p>Remains of catchwords.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Masorah, frequently written in the form of ornamental designs, occupies two lines in the upper margin and three lines in lower margin of the page.</p>
									<p>Several masoretic rubrics at the end of most of the books.</p>
									<p>Flesh side and hair side are distinguishable.
</p>
									<p>Parallel Hebrew foliation on the verso side.
</p>
									<p>The number of Psalms is 149 (114 and 115 regarded as one). </p>
									<p>Watermark, folio [ii recto] of the monogram 'IHS' with a cross, similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">1785a</ref>.</p>
									<p>Unfoliated blank leaf after folio 217r.
</p>
									<p>Watermark, folio [218r], of a fleur-de-lis in a crowned coat of arms and with the monogram 'WR', similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">1784/1785</ref> .</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, punctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">῾Ezra ben Ya῾aḳov ben Aderet</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, Castellon d’Ampurias, Elul 5156 [1396], folio 217v. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<summary>Numerous micrographical designs.</summary>
							<decoNote type="marginal">Numerous micrographical designs.</decoNote>
						</decoDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shemu᾿el ῾Alḳabets</name>: inscribed with his name ([218v]). </p>
							<p>Latin inscriptions: translation of the colophon; calculation of the Hebrew date in by the same hand, <date calendar="Gregorian">1708</date> (217v).</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">John Covel</name> (b. 1638, d. 1722), chaplain to the Levant Company at Constantinople: in his collection (no. VIII). His manuscripts were acquired for the Harley Collection for £300 in <date calendar="Gregorian">1716</date>. <name type="person" role="owner">Edward Harley</name>: bought by him, together with Covel's other manuscripts, for £300 on 2<date calendar="Gregorian">7 Feb. 1715/6</date> (<ref target="Wright_1972"/>); inscription by Harley's librarian, <name type="person">Humfrey Wanley</name>, 1<date calendar="Gregorian">8 January 1723/4</date> (1r).  </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p> 	Post-1600. Harleian binding of black buckram.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Biblia Hebraica. Tom III. Brit. Mus. Harley 5575.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
